    <note>Cheng(1) Zongyan [15565] See documentation for great grandson, Shuda [15569]. This is good example of successive generations when none of the direct patrilineal ancestors held office, but each generation is represented by at least one collateral jinshi. Moreover, for three generations the wives were selected from a Hu(1) family and none of the father-in-laws held office. Finally, Zongyan moved to Yixian, ancestral home of his father-in-law, Hu(1) Yuqing [15576]. However, according to CBD, Zongyan did hold office. CBD, 4, 3041.</note>
